<h1>@HI{{nikui}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> V@masustem{{}} <strong>@HI{{nikui}}</strong>
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<strong>@HI{{nikui}}</strong> is an auxiliary that adds a nuance of "difficult to do".
</br>
The combined form functions as an @HI{{i}}-adjective and inflects in the same way.
</br>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kono @KJ{{book}}ha @KJ{{large^unusual read}}mi<strong>nikui</strong>desu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      This book is very hard to read.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{east^capital}}ha @KJ{{live}}mi<strong>nikui</strong>desu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Living in Tokyo is difficult.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

